## Build a Dropdown Menu in React

**Mental Model:** The core idea is to manage the dropdown's visibility with a state variable. We'll use a button to toggle this state and an `onClick` handler on the document to close it when clicking outside. Keyboard navigation will involve `onKeyDown` handlers to manage focus and visibility.

### Step 1 — Basic Structure and State Management
Start by creating the `DropdownMenu` component with a state variable to control its open/closed status. The button will toggle this state, and the menu items will only render when open.

```jsx
import React, { useState } from 'react';

const DropdownMenu = () => {
  const [isOpen, setIsOpen] = useState(false);

  const toggleDropdown = () => setIsOpen(!isOpen);

  return (
    <div style={{ position: 'relative', display: 'inline-block' }}>
      <button onClick={toggleDropdown} aria-haspopup="true" aria-expanded={isOpen}>
        Toggle Dropdown
      </button>
      {isOpen && (
        <ul style={{
          position: 'absolute',
          listStyle: 'none',
          padding: 0,
          margin: '5px 0 0 0',
          border: '1px solid #ccc',
          backgroundColor: 'white',
          minWidth: '120px',
          zIndex: 100
        }}>
          <li><button style={{ width: '100%', padding: '8px 12px', border: 'none', background: 'none', textAlign: 'left', cursor: 'pointer' }}>Option 1</button></li>
          <li><button style={{ width: '100%', padding: '8px 12px', border: 'none', background: 'none', textAlign: 'left', cursor: 'pointer' }}>Option 2</button></li>
          <li><button style={{ width: '100%', padding: '8px 12px', border: 'none', background: 'none', textAlign: 'left', cursor: 'pointer' }}>Option 3</button></li>
        </ul>
      )}
    </div>
  );
};

export default DropdownMenu;
```

### Step 2 — Close on Outside Click
Implement a `useEffect` hook to add and remove an event listener to the document. This listener will close the dropdown if a click occurs outside the component's root element, using a `useRef` to reference the component.

```jsx
import React, { useState, useEffect, useRef } from 'react';

const DropdownMenu = () => {
  const [isOpen, setIsOpen] = useState(false);
  const dropdownRef = useRef(null);

  const toggleDropdown = () => setIsOpen(!isOpen);

  useEffect(() => {
    const handleClickOutside = (event) => {
      if (dropdownRef.current && !dropdownRef.current.contains(event.target)) {
        setIsOpen(false);
      }
    };

    document.addEventListener('mousedown', handleClickOutside);
    return () => {
      document.removeEventListener('mousedown', handleClickOutside);
    };
  }, [dropdownRef]);

  return (
    <div ref={dropdownRef} style={{ position: 'relative', display: 'inline-block' }}>
      <button onClick={toggleDropdown} aria-haspopup="true" aria-expanded={isOpen}>
        Toggle Dropdown
      </button>
      {isOpen && (
        <ul style={{
          position: 'absolute',
          listStyle: 'none',
          padding: 0,
          margin: '5px 0 0 0',
          border: '1px solid #ccc',
          backgroundColor: 'white',
          minWidth: '120px',
          zIndex: 100
        }}>
          <li><button style={{ width: '100%', padding: '8px 12px', border: 'none', background: 'none', textAlign: 'left', cursor: 'pointer' }}>Option 1</button></li>
          <li><button style={{ width: '100%', padding: '8px 12px', border: 'none', background: 'none', textAlign: 'left', cursor: 'pointer' }}>Option 2</button></li>
          <li><button style={{ width: '100%', padding: '8px 12px', border: 'none', background: 'none', textAlign: 'left', cursor: 'pointer' }}>Option 3</button></li>
        </ul>
      )}
    </div>
  );
};

export default DropdownMenu;
```

### Step 3 — Keyboard Navigation (Arrows, Enter, Escape)
Add `onKeyDown` handlers to the button and menu items. The Escape key should close the dropdown, Arrow Up/Down should navigate focus between items, and Enter should activate an item. When opening, focus should move to the first item.

```jsx
import React, { useState, useEffect, useRef } from 'react';

const DropdownMenu = () => {
  const [isOpen, setIsOpen] = useState(false);
  const dropdownRef = useRef(null);
  const menuItemsRef = useRef([]);

  const toggleDropdown = () => setIsOpen(!isOpen);

  const handleKeyDown = (event) => {
    if (event.key === 'Escape') {
      setIsOpen(false);
      dropdownRef.current.querySelector('button').focus(); // Focus back to toggle button
    } else if (event.key === 'ArrowDown' && !isOpen) {
      setIsOpen(true);
      event.preventDefault(); // Prevent page scroll
    } else if (event.key === 'Enter' || event.key === ' ') {
      if (!isOpen) {
        setIsOpen(true);
        event.preventDefault();
      }
    }
  };

  const handleMenuItemKeyDown = (event, index) => {
    if (event.key === 'ArrowDown') {
      event.preventDefault();
      const nextIndex = (index + 1) % menuItemsRef.current.length;
      menuItemsRef.current[nextIndex].focus();
    } else if (event.key === 'ArrowUp') {
      event.preventDefault();
      const prevIndex = (index - 1 + menuItemsRef.current.length) % menuItemsRef.current.length;
      menuItemsRef.current[prevIndex].focus();
    } else if (event.key === 'Escape') {
      setIsOpen(false);
      dropdownRef.current.querySelector('button').focus();
    } else if (event.key === 'Enter' || event.key === ' ') {
      event.preventDefault();
      // Simulate item activation
      alert(`Option ${index + 1} selected!`);
      setIsOpen(false);
      dropdownRef.current.querySelector('button').focus();
    }
  };

  useEffect(() => {
    const handleClickOutside = (event) => {
      if (dropdownRef.current && !dropdownRef.current.contains(event.target)) {
        setIsOpen(false);
      }
    };

    document.addEventListener('mousedown', handleClickOutside);
    return () => {
      document.removeEventListener('mousedown', handleClickOutside);
    };
  }, []);

  useEffect(() => {
    if (isOpen) {
      // Focus first item when dropdown opens
      menuItemsRef.current[0]?.focus();
    }
  }, [isOpen]);

  const options = ['Option 1', 'Option 2', 'Option 3'];

  return (
    <div ref={dropdownRef} style={{ position: 'relative', display: 'inline-block' }}>
      <button
        onClick={toggleDropdown}
        onKeyDown={handleKeyDown}
        aria-haspopup="true"
        aria-expanded={isOpen}
        style={{ padding: '8px 12px', cursor: 'pointer' }}
      >
        Toggle Dropdown
      </button>
      {isOpen && (
        <ul
          role="menu"
          style={{
            position: 'absolute',
            listStyle: 'none',
            padding: 0,
            margin: '5px 0 0 0',
            border: '1px solid #ccc',
            backgroundColor: 'white',
            minWidth: '120px',
            zIndex: 100,
            boxShadow: '0 2px 5px rgba(0,0,0,0.2)'
          }}
        >
          {options.map((option, index) => (
            <li key={index} role="none">
              <button
                ref={el => menuItemsRef.current[index] = el}
                role="menuitem"
                onClick={() => {
                  alert(`${option} selected!`);
                  setIsOpen(false);
                  dropdownRef.current.querySelector('button').focus();
                }}
                onKeyDown={(e) => handleMenuItemKeyDown(e, index)}
                tabIndex={0} // Make button focusable
                style={{ width: '100%', padding: '8px 12px', border: 'none', background: 'none', textAlign: 'left', cursor: 'pointer', outline: 'none' }}
                onFocus={(e) => e.target.style.backgroundColor = '#f0f0f0'}
                onBlur={(e) => e.target.style.backgroundColor = 'white'}
              >
                {option}
              </button>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      )}
    </div>
  );
};

export default DropdownMenu;
```

**Edge Cases:**

*   **Accessibility (ARIA attributes):** Ensure `aria-haspopup`, `aria-expanded`, `role="menu"`, and `role="menuitem"` are correctly used for screen readers.
*   **Focus Management:** When the dropdown closes (via Escape or selection), focus should return to the toggle button.
*   **Scroll Behavior:** Prevent page scrolling when using arrow keys to navigate menu items.
*   **Tab Key:** The Tab key should move focus out of the dropdown when it's open, or to the next focusable element after the toggle button when closed.

**Interview tip:** Emphasize your understanding of accessibility (ARIA roles, keyboard navigation) and proper cleanup in `useEffect` for event listeners. Discussing the `useRef` hook for DOM interaction is also a plus.

