Building a dropdown menu in Vue involves managing its visibility state, handling clicks outside the component to close it, and implementing keyboard navigation for accessibility.

### Step 1 — Basic Structure and Toggle Visibility
The core idea is to have a button that toggles the visibility of a menu list. We'll use a `ref` for the `isOpen` state and a method to toggle it.
```vue
<template>
  <div class="dropdown">
    <button @click="toggleDropdown" aria-haspopup="true" :aria-expanded="isOpen.toString()">
      Toggle Dropdown
    </button>
    <ul v-if="isOpen" class="dropdown-menu">
      <li><a href="#">Item 1</a></li>
      <li><a href="#">Item 2</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</template>

<script setup>
import { ref } from 'vue';

const isOpen = ref(false);
const toggleDropdown = () => {
  isOpen.value = !isOpen.value;
};
</script>
```

### Step 2 — Close on Click Outside
To close the dropdown when a user clicks anywhere outside of it, we attach a global click listener. We need to check if the click target is outside the dropdown's root element.
```vue
<template>
  <div ref="dropdownRef" class="dropdown">
    <button @click="toggleDropdown" aria-haspopup="true" :aria-expanded="isOpen.toString()">
      Toggle Dropdown
    </button>
    <ul v-if="isOpen" class="dropdown-menu">
      <li><a href="#">Item 1</a></li>
      <li><a href="#">Item 2</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</template>

<script setup>
import { ref, onMounted, onUnmounted } from 'vue';

const isOpen = ref(false);
const dropdownRef = ref(null);

const toggleDropdown = () => {
  isOpen.value = !isOpen.value;
};

const handleClickOutside = (event) => {
  if (dropdownRef.value && !dropdownRef.value.contains(event.target)) {
    isOpen.value = false;
  }
};

onMounted(() => {
  document.addEventListener('click', handleClickOutside);
});

onUnmounted(() => {
  document.removeEventListener('click', handleClickOutside);
});
</script>
```

### Step 3 — Keyboard Navigation (Arrow Keys and Escape)
For accessibility, implement keyboard navigation. Arrow keys should move focus between menu items, and `Escape` should close the dropdown.
```vue
<template>
  <div ref="dropdownRef" class="dropdown" @keydown="handleKeydown">
    <button ref="triggerRef" @click="toggleDropdown" aria-haspopup="true" :aria-expanded="isOpen.toString()">
      Toggle Dropdown
    </button>
    <ul v-if="isOpen" class="dropdown-menu" role="menu" tabindex="-1">
      <li v-for="(item, index) in items" :key="item.id">
        <a :ref="el => { if (el) menuItemsRefs[index] = el; }" :href="item.href" role="menuitem" tabindex="-1">{{ item.label }}</a>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</template>

<script setup>
import { ref, onMounted, onUnmounted, nextTick } from 'vue';

const isOpen = ref(false);
const dropdownRef = ref(null);
const triggerRef = ref(null);
const menuItemsRefs = ref([]);
const focusedIndex = ref(-1);

const items = ref([
  { id: 1, label: 'Item 1', href: '#' },
  { id: 2, label: 'Item 2', href: '#' },
  { id: 3, label: 'Item 3', href: '#' }
]);

const toggleDropdown = async () => {
  isOpen.value = !isOpen.value;
  if (isOpen.value) {
    await nextTick();
    focusedIndex.value = -1; // Reset focus when opening
  }
};

const handleClickOutside = (event) => {
  if (dropdownRef.value && !dropdownRef.value.contains(event.target)) {
    isOpen.value = false;
  }
};

const handleKeydown = (event) => {
  if (!isOpen.value) return;

  const menuItems = menuItemsRefs.value.filter(Boolean);
  const numItems = menuItems.length;

  switch (event.key) {
    case 'Escape':
      isOpen.value = false;
      triggerRef.value.focus();
      break;
    case 'ArrowDown':
      event.preventDefault();
      focusedIndex.value = (focusedIndex.value + 1) % numItems;
      menuItems[focusedIndex.value].focus();
      break;
    case 'ArrowUp':
      event.preventDefault();
      focusedIndex.value = (focusedIndex.value - 1 + numItems) % numItems;
      menuItems[focusedIndex.value].focus();
      break;
    case 'Tab':
      // Allow default tab behavior to move out of the dropdown
      isOpen.value = false;
      break;
  }
};

onMounted(() => {
  document.addEventListener('click', handleClickOutside);
});

onUnmounted(() => {
  document.removeEventListener('click', handleClickOutside);
});
</script>

